                  <summary source="#WinternitzKeith1905">The Rudravidhāna, a manual of Śiva worship, purporting to be according to Śāṅkhāyana’s school</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="sa">Sanskrit.</textLang>
                  <msItem> 
                     <title/>
                     
                  <incipit source="#WinternitzKeith1905">śrīgaṇeśāya namaḥ | oṃ atha Śāṅkhāyanīśākhoktaṃ Rudravidhānaṃ likhyate | acamanaṃ | prāṇayāmaḥ | oṃ hrāṃ ātatvāya svāhā | oṃ hriṃ vidyātatvāya namaḥ | iti Śiṣṭāmnāyānusṛṣṭaṃ Rudravidhānaṃ | Caṃdanā Garu (added by later hand) Karpūra Kastarī Kuṃkumāni ca | sugaṃdhidravyamity uktam amnāto yakṣakardamāḥ ǁ 1 ǁ vṛṣaṃ caṃḍaṃ vṛṣaṃ caiva somasūtraṃ punar vṛṣaṃ | caṃḍaṃ ca somasūtraṃ ca punaś caṃḍaṃ punar vṛṣaṃ ǁ 1 ǁ Rudro Ghoraḥ Paśupati Virūpo viśvarūpakaḥ |</incipit><explicit source="#WinternitzKeith1905"><locus>[34v] </locus>Tryaṃbakaś ca Kaparddī ca Śūlapāṇis tu Bhairavaḥ | īśānaś ca Maheśāno Rudrā ekādaśā smṛtāḥ ǁ ity ekādaśarudranāmāni |</explicit></msItem>
